The President said the borders and airspace will remain closed except for cargo, diplomats and those seeking treatment abroad. He said the rising cases were "worrisome", Anadolu news agency reports. The country has recorded nearly 700 cases including 16 deaths. The vice-president and three ministers are among those infected by the virus, but the president tested negative on Monday. Worship places remain closed in the country and schools will only allow final year students to sit for exit examinations from August 17. All markets and shopping areas will close every Sunday for cleaning and fumigation. --BBC--